Description: Wayland-Native Virtualization & Container Manager
 Nova is a high-performance virtualization and container orchestration
 platform built entirely in Rust. It unifies KVM/QEMU virtual machines,
 lightweight containers, and software-defined networking under a single
 declarative interface.
 .
 Key features:
  - Zero-overhead Rust runtime
  - Enterprise KVM/QEMU virtualization with GPU passthrough
  - Lightweight container technology
  - Infrastructure as Code with TOML configuration
  - Software-defined networking
  - Native Wayland GUI
  - Security-first design
 .
 Perfect for AI/ML workloads, development environments, and production
 deployments on Debian-based systems including Pop!_OS and Ubuntu.

Package: nova-virtualization-gui
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         nova-virtualization (= ${binary:Version}),
         libgtk-4-1,
         libwayland-client0
Description: Wayland-Native GUI for Nova Virtualization Manager
 This package provides the graphical user interface for Nova, a modern
 virtualization management platform.
 .
 The GUI is built with GTK4 and native Wayland support, providing:
  - Real-time VM/container monitoring
  - Interactive network topology visualization
  - Template gallery and wizard
  - GPU passthrough configuration
  - Storage pool management
